openclinxr visual qa temporal eye fixture placeholder
This deterministic fixture is intentionally larger than the tiny-placeholder guard used by the visual QA evidence checker.
It is not clinical evidence, not Quest evidence, not production video evidence, and not proof of humanoid realism quality.
It exists only to exercise the evidence contract that permits video artifacts to carry temporal blink and micro-saccade review.
Future generated or headset-captured videos should replace this fixture when judging actual actor eye realism.
The checker separately blocks still screenshots from claiming temporal blink or micro-saccade pass status.
Frame 000: eyes open, gaze toward learner camera, mouth phoneme active.
Frame 001: eyelids begin deterministic blink closure, gaze remains target-aligned.
Frame 002: eyelids closed at blink apex, micro-saccade yaw perturbation recorded.
Frame 003: eyes reopen, micro-saccade pitch settles, dialogue viseme continues.
Frame 004: gaze target remains actor or learner according to encounter turn metadata.
Frame 005: blink cycle completed; no production ocular animation claim is made.
This file is textual fixture content with a webm extension and should never be used as visual proof.
The contract-level test only requires size and metadata gates; real visual QA must provide actual video evidence.
Temporal evidence pass claims require a video artifact, not this placeholder fixture in production review.
